# Structural Rotation: Exercise

<div id="outcomes"><details><summary></summary>

* Trace the balancing operations of an AVL tree.

</details></div>

<span class="tag">Exercise</span> Starting from an empty BST, perform the following operations in order. Apply structural rotations, if needed, to keep the BST balanced.

```text
insert(15)
insert(20)
insert(24)
insert(10)
insert(13)
insert(7)
insert(30)
insert(36)
insert(25)
remove(24)
remove(20)
```

<details class="solution" data-release="Mar 27, 2023 17:00:00">
<summary>Solution</summary>

Visit [this interactive visualizer](https://www.cs.usfca.edu/~galles/visualization/AVLtree.html) and carry out the operations.

The final BST should look like this:

<div class="center">
<img src="/img/19/avl52.png" width="80%">
</div>

</details>
